%I A393906 #13 Mar 07 2026 04:49:54
%S A393906 1,1,3,14,77,475,3188,22004,156230,1126536,8226592,60653744
%N A393906 Equivalence classes of clusters of n connected lozenges in the triangular grid.
%C A393906 Lozenges are connected in the sense that they share edges, but must not overlap. This is a variant of A056845: Here equivalence considers clusters applying the reduced symmetry point group of C_6, which means clusters that can be mapped by using reflections are distinct (unless they can be mapped by pure rotations...)
%C A393906 a(n) grows roughly twice as fast as A056845(n) because at large n the clusters which are mirror-symmetric are only a small set of all clusters.
%H A393906 R. J. Mathar, <a href="/A056845/a056845.pdf">Illustrations</a>
%Y A393906 Cf. A056845.
